      "name": "High-fidelity CFD hemolysis index validation result",
      "description": "Hemolysis index predictions from the CFD model were compared against reference values derived from a companion high-fidelity numerical simulation of the FDA generic pump geometry. The simulation employed the same Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage model and identical boundary conditions as would be used in a physical experiment. Predicted HI values fell within 8% of the reference across all five operating points, which the assessment team characterises as equivalent in evidentiary weight to a physical bench experiment given the maturity of the flow solver and the availability of detailed grid-convergence data.",
