    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the high-fidelity numerical simulation provides validation evidence of sufficient fidelity to satisfy the hemolysis credibility requirements, noting that the simulation employed the same governing equations, mesh density, and boundary conditions as would be used in a physical bench experiment. The team characterised the 8% agreement across all five operating points as equivalent in evidentiary weight to experimental data. On this basis the package was accepted. Note: the structured requirement (requiredVerificationMethod: experimental-validation) is not satisfied by the activityType (numerical-simulation) of the supporting activity; this inference gap constitutes weakener W-AR-03.",
